description:
In Episode 204 of Mike Finnegan's Garage we hang out at Motor Trend's Roadkill Nights event, which is powered by Dodge. The event is unique because the city of Pontiac, Michigan, allows Roadkill to hold street legal drag racing right on Woodward ave. Newbern and I drove the Roadkill ramp truck there while hauling precious cargo as part of a really cool upcoming episode of Roadkill, which you can see of Motor Trend Plus streaming app. Rather than drive all the way back home to Georgia with an empty ramp truck, we decided to buy a really rusty and slightly butchered pro street 1970 Dodge Charger. The car is a mess but I have a vision and a few used speed parts that will someday go on this car. In the meantime, enjoy the trip and the fun of celebrating Mike Cotten's new car that he bought at RKN as well! 
Want to help support this channel? Buy our merch and we'll spend all of your cash on making more videos and bad decisions involving cars, trucks, boats, jet skis etc. Thanks!
-Finnegan

My husband Dave and I discovered this abandoned survival bunker on land we bought in Interior Alaska. It had been occupied by a prepper it seemed, and then left to the elements with a bad roof for decades.

It seemed very daunting to clean it up after our first effort, and we let it sit a few weeks, deciding what to do with it. (Clean it up? Burn it? Leave it and move on to working the better part of the property?)

Originally from Nashville, Tennessee, we got married 2013 and were super ‚Äúnormal.‚Äù I was a teacher and Nate started a small printing business from the spare bedroom of our apartment. We discovered the world of ‚Äútravel hacking‚Äù & became obsessed. So after 2 years of obsessively saving $35k and over 2 million miles and points, we sold our cars and apartment and left home January 10, 2016 for a ‚Äúone year‚Äù trip around the world. Our goal was to see as many places as possible before we ran out of money and went home to ‚Äúnormal life.‚Äù We started this travel vlog to share our experiences with friends and family, but quickly fell in love with this lifestyle and did everything we could to keep going. 4 years later, we achieved our new goal of visiting 100 countries and all 7 continents. We had no plans to slow down, until 2020 forced us to ;) Which is when we bought a converted van to start exploring our own country for the first time. Van life was a major adjustment and so different than flying every week like we were used to, but we are incredibly thankful to be able to continue doing something we love every day. üòäüé•üåé

Prior to ‚ÄúHappy Anywhere‚Äù Shelton celebrated a 2x Platinum, multi-week No. 1 with ‚ÄúNobody But You,‚Äù which has now surpassed 280 million streams. The single made its TV debut on the 62nd GRAMMY Awards, where Shelton was also nominated for Best Country Solo Performance for his hit ‚ÄúGod‚Äôs Country.‚Äù The 4x Platinum smash earned the 2019 CMA Award and 2020 ACM Award for Single of the Year. As his award wins approach the hundreds, Shelton remains a force in the industry with ACM (5), AMA (3), CMA (10), CMT (11) and People‚Äôs Choice Awards (7), among many others. He recently wrapped his headlining ‚ÄúFriends and Heroes 2021‚Äù tour with Lindsay Ell and special appearances by Martina McBride, Tracy Byrd and Trace Adkins.

As a coach for the Emmy Award-winning television show The Voice, Shelton is an eight-time champion, most recently with his contestant Cam Anthony. The Grand Ole Opry member also remains focused on his Ole Red partnership with Ryman Hospitality, with locations currently in Tishomingo, Nashville, Gatlinburg and Orlando. A noted humanitarian, Shelton has helped raise millions of dollars for children‚Äôs hospitals, disaster relief organizations, food banks and more in his home state of Oklahoma and throughout the entire country.

description:
Cooking My Favourite Meal With My Sister! Easily one of my best go to meals to cook, packed with protein and easy to make.

Try this power bowl and let me know your thoughts! 

Power Bowl Recipe:
Servings: 3 

Ingredients: 
SALMON INGREDIENTS: 
 ‚ÅÉ 3 salmon filets 
 ‚ÅÉ 2 tbsp olive oil 
 ‚ÅÉ Seasoning 1-2 tbsp each = lemon pepper, paprika, salt, pepper, garlic powder 

SWEET POTATOES: 
 ‚ÅÉ 2 sweet potatoes peeled (Season with olive oil, salt, pepper, garlic powder) 

SWEET POTATO SAUCE: 
 ‚ÅÉ 2 tbsp honey 
 ‚ÅÉ 2 tbsp red wine vinegar 
 ‚ÅÉ 1 squirt of siracha 
 ‚ÅÉ 1/4 cup buffalo sauce 

POWER BOWL TOPPINGS: 
 ‚ÅÉ 1 long cucumber peeled & cut 
 ‚ÅÉ Brown rice (1 cup each serving)
 ‚ÅÉ About 3 cups of arugula 
 ‚ÅÉ 3 avocados 
 ‚ÅÉ 3 cups mushrooms (season with salt, pepper, olive oil, garlic powder) 

GREEN GODDESS DRESSING: 
 ‚ÅÉ 1 cup cilantro 
 ‚ÅÉ 1 cup parsley 
 ‚ÅÉ 1/2 cup mint 
 ‚ÅÉ 1/2 cup basil 
 ‚ÅÉ 1/2 cup Olive oil 
 ‚ÅÉ 1 clove garlic 
 ‚ÅÉ 1 lime 

HOW TO: 
1. Start off by washing & cutting/ chopping all your ingredients, cilantro, basil, mint, parsley. 
2. Peel your cucumber and sweet potatoes, cut cucumbers into cubes and sweet potatoes into one inch bites.
3. After all the ingredients are chopped, start making your green goddess dressing in the food processor by adding in the cilantro, parsley, basil, mint, olive oil, garlic, salt and pepper, and lime.
4. Pre heat the oven to 425 after you finish making the dressing. start seasoning the sweet potatoes & mushrooms. 
5. Once the sweet potatoes and mushrooms are seasoned, place the sweet potatoes on a baking sheet with olive oil & aluminum so they don‚Äôt stick. Pop in microwave for about 15-20 minutes and flip them half way. 
6. Once you pop the sweet potatoes in the oven start seasoning your fish. 
7. Season all the fish to taste and start heating up your pans so you can cook the mushrooms & salmon.
8. Once the pans are hot, add your mushrooms and fish. Use two different pans, but if you only have one pan, cook the mushrooms first and then the fish. Cook the fish for about 3-5 minutes on each side on medium to low heat and cover the pan, make sure you are checking it so you don‚Äôt over cook it. Cook your mushrooms for about 5-10 minutes (or however you like them cooked) while your fish is cooking.
9. Make sure you don‚Äôt forget to flip the sweet potatoes half way. Once everything is done cooking, let sweet potatoes cool off and start making the sweet potato sauce. Once sweet potatoes are cool, add the sauce and then start adding on the rest of the toppings. Enjoy for meal prep, post workout meal, or if you‚Äôre just craving a flavorful dish. Hope you enjoy it!!!ü§ç

An impossible journey, all in the name of friendship. Based on a true story, The Greatest Beer Run Ever premieres September 30 in theaters and streaming on Apple TV+ https://apple.co/_TheGreatestBeerRunEver 

Chickie (Zac Efron) wants to support his friends fighting in Vietnam, so he does something wild‚Äîpersonally bring them American beer. What starts as a well-meaning journey quickly changes Chickie‚Äôs life and perspective. Based on a true story.

Hailing from Skydance Media, screenplay is adapted by Peter Farrelly, Brian Currie and Pete Jones, and is based on the book The Greatest Beer Run Ever: A Memoir of Friendship, Loyalty and War, by Joanna Molloy and John ‚ÄúChickie‚Äù Donohue. Peter Farrelly as Director. Producers are David Ellison, Dana Goldberg and Don Granger on behalf of Skydance, with Andrew Muscato and Jake Myers. The book/source material became a New York Times best seller when it was published in 2020 and generated stories of this journey across a wide spectrum of media and news programming.
